- Welcome to Virgulas!
  Virgulas is a local-first browser outliner — an infinite tree of editable nodes.
- This intro lives only in memory. Your changes here are not saved.
  Open **Options → Upgrade storage** to keep your data permanently.
  - Click any node to focus it and start editing.
    Press **Enter** to create a new node below.
    Press **Escape** to stop editing and return to navigation mode.
  - Text supports **bold**, __italic__, `monospace`, and [links](https://virgulas.com)
    Markdown is rendered when not editing — click to see the raw text
    Links open in a new tab/window when clicked
  - Use `#tags` and `@mentions` inline (example: #todo and @alice)
    They render as rounded pills; click one to start Search with that token
  - Each node can also have a description (this is one!)
    Press `Shift+Enter` while editing to toggle between the node title and its description
    The description is hidden when empty and shows only the first 2 lines when not editing
- Organising your outline
  - Indent and unindent nodes with `Tab` / `Shift+Tab`
  - Move nodes up and down with `Alt+↑` / `Alt+↓`
  - Collapse and expand children with `Ctrl+Space` or the ▶/▼ button at the end of each line
    Or use the shortcut `Ctrl+Space`
  + Collapsed node example
    - Child A
    - Child B
    - Child C
- Zoom
  Click the ● bullet of any node to zoom into it — its children become the new root view.
  
  - A breadcrumb at the top shows your location in the tree; click any segment to zoom back out.
    On desktop, use **Alt+→** to zoom in and **Alt+←** to zoom out.
- Multi-select
  Focus a node, then hold **Shift** and press **↑** or **↓** to extend the selection
  to other nodes at the same indentation level.
  - Multi-selected nodes can be moved, indented, or deleted all at once.
+ Search
  Press **Escape** when no node is focused (desktop) to open the search bar.
  On mobile, tap the **Search** button in the bottom status bar.
  - Non-matching nodes are hidden; matching text is highlighted.
  - Use **Tab** / **Shift+Tab** to cycle through results.
  - Press **Enter** or click a result to zoom into the closest ancestor of the match.
  - Press **Escape** again to dismiss search.
- Raw mode
  Click **Raw** in the bottom toolbar to edit the outline as plain VMD text (Virgulas MarkDown).
  Lines starting with `-` are expanded nodes; `+` are collapsed nodes.
  - Indentation determines hierarchy — a child just needs more leading space than its parent.
- Keyboard shortcuts
  See the full list of shortcuts with the **?** button in the bottom toolbar.
- Storage options
  This document is stored only in memory and will be lost when you close this tab.
  Open **Options → Upgrade storage** to switch to a persistent mode:
  - **Local** — document encrypted in your browser with a passphrase you choose
  - **Remote** — encrypted and synced to the cloud (requires a free account)
  - **File** — saved as a plain `.vmd` file on your computer (no passphrase needed)
